                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-152-off939 t18211205-152-crimeloc942"></join>. On the 30th of November I was in my back parlour, the shop door was open; I heard a person come in, looked through the glass door and saw the prisoner take a piece of bacon out of the window and go out. He heard me following him, and dropped it on the pavement. I secured him on the other side of the way.</p>
